At the moment, there are two ways to create JIRA issues with a CSV import: 
- the more limited [Creating issues using the CSV importer|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/Cloud/Creating+issues+using+the+CSV+importer], not allowing users to create new entities from field values (e.g. new users or versions);
- [Importing Data from CSV|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/Cloud/Importing+Data+from+CSV], only available for JIRA Administrators and providing more flexibility.

At the moment, the first functionality can be accessed from the top bar menu under *Issues > Import Issues from CSV*, which can be misleading. The documentation for the differentiates between "creating" and "importing" issues from CSV - it would help if the application itself reflected this distinction too.

