In earlier versions of JIRA, a user could bookmark a project and easily navigate from issue to issue by simply editing the location bar.

For example, a URL would like like this: {{http://jira_server.local:8080/browse/SIMPLE}} and to go to a particular issue a user only needed to add {{-105}} to the location bar to navigate to a particular issue.

Now, a user has to bookmark a particular issue in order to do this, because there is no simple URL at the top level of the project, anymore. Having a project's top level browser URL location with less additional text (currently it's a variant of {{/?selectedTab=com.atlassian.jira.jira-projects-plugin:issues-panel}} that's added to the URL would make doing this easier.

